<HEADLINE>
FT  19 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Enviromed makes Pounds 7.4m buy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Enviromed, the biotechnology group, has bought F&amp;H Baxter (Holdings), a
dental equipment and supplies company, for Pounds 7.42m.
Enviromed also proposes to raise Pounds 2.7m by the placing and open offer
of 3.6m 8 per cent convertible redeemable preference shares at 100p. The
shares are being offered to existing shareholders on the basis of two for
every 13 ordinary shares.
The acquisition will be satisfied as to Pounds 2.1m by the issue of 1.7m
ordinary shares, Pounds 3.72m in variable rate guaranteed unsecured loan
notes, and Pounds 1.6m in cash. Of the cash consideration, Pounds 1.38m will
be deferred until the Inland Revenue agrees to offset Baxter's advance
corporation tax liability arising before September 1994 against mainstream
corporation tax.
Turnover for Baxter for the year ended August 31 1993 was Pounds 19.1m
(Pounds 18.2m) for pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.3m (Pounds 1.59m).
</TEXT>
