FT  19 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In a week which saw some D-Mark weakness against other currencies, the
D-Mark managed to hang on to its third place in the EMS grid. Its spread
against the peseta, the weakest currency in the system, fell to 4.89 per
cent from just over 5 per cent. Currencies, Page 37
The chart shows the member currencies of the exchange rate mechanism
measured against the weakest currency in the system. Most of the currencies
are permitted to fluctuate within 15 per cent of agreed central rates
against the other members of the mechanism. The exceptions are the D-Mark
and the guilder which move in a 2.25 per cent band.
