</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The London equity market fell sharply following the release of unexpectedly
strong data on the US economy. The FT-SE 100 Index ended the day 47.6 points
down at 3,065.1, its largest daily fall since mid-June. The Footsie fell
nearly 2.4 per cent on the week as the first rise in base rates for nearly
five years left the UK bond markets still vulnerable to shocks from
overseas.
