<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices for finer Merinos rose even more rapidly in the earlier Australian
sale days this week, with broader types also rising if more gradually. The
Eastern states market indicator ended at 829c/kg, compared with 780c/kg a
week before. The Western states indicator rose strongly at the first
Fremantle sale but the market was a little erratic at the close, 5 cents
down on the day if still 25 cents higher than at the end of last week. With
prices at least double those a year ago, and for finer Merinos much more
than that, ther is resistance among wool textile manufactures and
particularly UK home market retailers, but a rising market does involve
small-scale but steady support even during the unhappier times.
The spices report was not available for this edition.
</TEXT>
