<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Fired Earth back in black at Pounds 60,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite virtual stagnation in the underlying market for ceramic tiles, Fired
Earth reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 60,000 for the six months to June
30, compared with a loss of Pounds 94,000.
Turnover was up slightly from Pounds 2.26m to Pounds 2.52m.
Earnings per share were 0.78p (1.25p losses).
Mr Nicholas Kneale, the chairman, said that lower costs and the 'gathering
momentum' of sales of new product lines in natural floor coverings had
helped the company move back into the black.
