<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 94 / International Company News: Swiss insurer on course for
'good' year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Zurich Insurance, one of the world's largest insurers, said its gross
premium income rose 1.4 per cent in the first half, to SFr14.2bn (Dollars
11.1bn). All three business areas - life, non-life and reinsurance - grew at
roughly the same rate.
Losses resulting from natural catastrophes were considerably higher than in
the comparable period in 1993. The group said insurance and assumed
reinsurance claims arising from the California earthquake earlier this year
would reach between Dollars 85m and Dollars 90m.
The life insurance division made a greater contribution to growth than in
recent years.
The group published no profit figure for the first half, but said it
expected a 'good overall result' in the full year, provided there were no
extraordinary developments on the claims, foreign exchange or financial
fronts.
The strength of the Swiss franc restrained premium growth rate in the first
half.
